{"id":"2303.08376","submitter":"Hao Xu","authors":"Hao Xu, Chia-Min Chung, Mingpu Qin, Ulrich Schollw\\\"ock, Steven R.\n  White, Shiwei Zhang","title":"Coexistence of superconductivity with partially filled stripes in the\n  Hubbard model","comments":"9 pages, 6 figures, with supplementary materials","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.supr-con cond-mat.str-el physics.comp-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Combining the complementary capabilities of two of the most powerful modern\ncomputational methods, we find superconductivity in both the electron- and\nhole-doped regimes of the two-dimensional Hubbard model (with next nearest\nneighbor hopping). In the electron-doped regime, superconductivity is weaker\nand is accompanied by antiferromagnetic N\\'eel correlations at low doping. The\nstrong superconductivity on the hole-doped side coexists with stripe order,\nwhich persists into the overdoped region with weaker hole density modulation.\nThese stripe orders, neither filled as in the pure Hubbard model (no next\nnearest neighbor hopping) nor half-filled as seen in previous state-of-the-art\ncalculations, vary in fillings between 0.6 and 0.8. The resolution of the tiny\nenergy scales separating competing orders requires exceedingly high accuracy\ncombined with averaging and extrapolating with a wide range of system sizes and\nboundary conditions. These results validate the applicability of this iconic\nmodel for describing cuprate high-$T_c$ superconductivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 05:29:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-16"}
