{"id":"2303.08436","submitter":"Christian Le Merdy","authors":"Charles Duquet, Christian Le Merdy","title":"A characterization of absolutely dilatable Schur multipliers","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OA math.FA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $M$ be a von Neumann algebra equipped with a normal semi-finite faithful\ntrace (nsf trace in short) and let $T\\colon M\\to M$ be a contraction. We say\nthat $T$ is absolutely dilatable if there exist another von Neumann algebra\n$M'$ equipped with a nsf trace, a $w^*$-continuous trace preserving unital\n$*$-homomorphim $J\\colon M\\to M'$ and a trace preserving $*$-automomorphim\n$U\\colon M'\\to M'$ such that $T^k=E U^k J$ for all integer $k\\geq 0$, where\n$E\\colon M'\\to M$ is the conditional expectation associated with $J$. Given a\n$\\sigma$-finite measure space $(\\Omega,\\mu)$, we characterize bounded Schur\nmultipliers $\\phi\\in L^\\infty(\\Omega^2)$ such that the Schur multiplication\noperator $T_\\phi\\colon B(L^2(\\Omega))\\to B(L^2(\\Omega))$ is absolutely\ndilatable. In the separable case, they are characterized by the existence of a\nvon Neumann algebra $N$ with a separable predual, equipped with a normalized\nnormal faithful trace $\\tau_N$, and of a $w^*$-continuous essentially bounded\nfunction $d\\colon\\Omega\\to N$ such that $\\phi(s,t)=\\tau_N(d(s)^*d(t))$ for\nalmost every $(s,t)\\in\\Omega^2$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 15 Mar 2023 08:19:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-16"}
